RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 50. Allowance Purse 14288. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 30 Allowed 1 lbs. A Race Since May 15 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 15 Allowed 4 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRECIOUS MEADOW bit in air, led throughout. DANIELITA R stalked pace, bid, second best. LACROSSE step slow. CHILD MEMORIES failed to menace.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 47. Allowance Purse 11270. FOR NATIVE FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 15 Allowed 1 lbs. A Race Since April 15 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAXIMA LARISSA led to 1/4 pole, second best. SIGMA ALPHA pressed pace, weakened. CAZADORA REAL broke sharply, chased, led 1/4 pole, drew clear. WILNELIS off slowly, gamely fourth rail. COPA DE ORO circled field 5 wide, late gain for place.

ENTRY.NAME: Cazadora Real
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke sharply, chased, led 1/4 pole, drew clear,

ENTRY.NAME: Copa de Oro
ENTRY.COMMENT: circled field 5 wide, late gain for place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 8100. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 122 lbs. 2# A clasf.$20,000 Allowed 2 lbs. 4# A clasf. inferiores y debts Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAN ICE failed to menace. DIENTE D'ORO failed to menace. SHOTGUN BILLIE led to 3/8 pole, tired. MOUSEFAST chased, led 3/8 pole, prevailed. MASTER OF THE NILE stumbled start, late kick 3 wide, short. DON DANY R. bit slow early, no menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Master of the Nile
ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled start, late kick 3 wide, short

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 46. Allowance Purse 11270. FOR NATIVE THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 118 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 15 Allowed 1 lbs. A Race Since April 15 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PETROLERO led throughout. CARLOS EL CANTANTE loomed 1/4 pole, 5 wide, couldn't match. EL FERROCARRIL off slowly, circled field 6 wide. CATALIZADOR bold move 500, split 1/4, flattened out. COMPOSITOR pressed pace inside, hustled along, weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Compositor
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace inside, hustled along, weakened,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 30 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since May 15 Allowed 4 lbs. A Race Since April 15 Allowed 7 lbs. Claiming Price $14,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JLO CAN DANCE off pace, rail, up late. PAPA'S LITTLE GIRL alternated lead, led stretch, caught. DANCIN DEE alternated lead, dueled, lost whip late. NEGOCIADORA L R step slow, some late gain. FAST N GONE pressed pace outside, gave way. RENEESDREAMGIRL step slow, mild rally 1/4 pole, flattened out. QUEEN CUPID failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Dancin Dee
ENTRY.COMMENT: alternated lead, dueled, lost whip late,

ENTRY.NAME: Reneesdreamgirl
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, mild rally 1/4 pole, flattened out,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 6000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JUNE 15 AND WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS. Weight, 121 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 30 Allowed 1 lbs. A Race Since May 15 Allowed 3 lbs . A Race Since April 15 Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BACCARAT HONOR stalked pace, rallied, drew off. MAREMAR set pace, second best. DREAM OF KINGDOM off pace, improved position. LADY ALEXANDRIA off pace, no rally. FRAN'S SALSA chased, weakened. PRINCESS MILEY slow early, weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 23. Maiden Claiming Purse 8600. FOR NATIVE MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 120 lbs. 1# A clasf.$20,000 Allowed 1 lbs. 2# A clasf. inferiores y debts Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUVENILIA close up, hustled along, up late. TEMBLOROSA set pace, couldn't contain winner. BEER BEAUTY pressed pace, mild bid between horses, angled in stretch, empty. AMAYA BESITO off slowly, 5 wide. ESPERANZA DE DOS off slowly, 6 wide. LA QUE NADIE QUISO circled field 7 wide. CHULERIA failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Beer Beauty
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, mild bid between horses, angled in stretch, empty,

ENTRY.NAME: Juvenilia
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up, hustled along, up late
